name: kendrick mcdaniel
summary:
ON JUNE 24, 2012 AT ABOUT 10:00 A.M., COMP, WHO IS A DALLAS POLICE OFFICER IN FULL
DALLAS POLICE UNIFORM WENT TO 4345 WEST CAMP WISDOM AT THE TACO BELL TO GET SOME
FOOD. WHILE INSIDE OF THE RESTAURANT, COMP OBSERVED A/P WAS SITTING WITH A/C 1
AND A/C 2 EATING THEIR FOOD. COMP OBSERVED THAT A/P WAS ACTING NERVOUS AND
FIDGETING AT THE TABLE. COMP STATED THAT A/P STOOD UP THAT HE WAS APPROXIMATELY
FIVE TO SEVEN FEET IN FRONT OF HIM. COMP OBSERVED A BROWN MARIJUANA CIGAR ABOVE
A/P'S EAR, AT WHICH TIME, COMP ORDERED A/P TO WALK TOWARDS HIM. A/P STATED TO
COMP, "FUCK YOU WE AIN'T GOT NOTHING TO TALK ABOUT". COMP CONTINUED WITH LOUD
VERBAL COMMANDS TO COME TO HIM. COMP STATED FOR HIS SAFETY, HE PULLED OUT HIS
DUTY WEAPON. A/P TOOK OFF RUNNING, JUMPING OVER A RAIL INSIDE OF THE STORE. COMP
STATED HE OBSERVED A/P PULL A BLACK HANDGUN FROM HIS WAISTBAND AND POINTED IT AT
COMP'S DIRECTION. COMP FIRED TWO SHOTS IN A/P'S DIRECTION STRIKING A/P IN THE
STOMACH. COMP HANDCUFFED A/P, WHO WAS LAYING ON THE FLOOR AND CALLED FOR ASSIST
OVER HIS HANDHELD POLICE RADIO. - R/O ROSALES 6771 ARRIVED ON THE SCENE AND
OBSERVED COMP HOLDING THREE
(3) SUSPECTS AT GUNPOINT. - A/P WAS TRANSPORTED TO METHODIST CENTRAL HOSPITAL BY
DFR 749. - CAPERS DET DAVISON 4267 WAS NOTIFIED AND CAME OUT TO THE OFFENSE
LOCATION. - THE A/CS WERE TRANSPORTED TO CAPERS TO BE INTERVIEWED.

name: stoney eugene rawlinson
hispanicorlatinoorigin: Not of Hispanic or Latino origin
summary:
"""Dallas police said they received word that 39-year old Stoney Eugene Rawlinson, a person of interest in a homicide, wanted to turn himself in to police.
According to Dallas police, arrangements were made for the man to meet with uniformed officers in a parking lot in the 6500 block of Skillman Avenue near Abrams Road.When officers arrived they said the man was sitting inside his car armed with a gun, according to his father, Stoney Eugene Rawlinson Sr., it was a 12-gauge shotgun. 
""The officers gave loud verbal commands for the suspect to drop his weapon, Dallas Police Sr. Cpl. Demarquis Black said. ""The suspect pointed his weapon at the officers, and fearing for their lives they fired their weapons."" """
